http://www.techhomethebacon.com/how-to/how-to-install-tor-on-backtrack-5r3.html

1. Add this line to your /etc/apt/sources.list file:
deb http://deb.torproject.org/torproject.org lucid main

2. Run these next two commands
gpg --keyserver keys.gnupg.net --recv 886DDD89
gpg --export A3C4F0F979CAA22CDBA8F512EE8CBC9E886DDD89 | sudo apt-key add -

3. Refresh your sources
apt-get update

4. Add to keyring
apt-get install deb.torproject.org-keyring

5. Install Tor:
apt-get install tor

6. Install Vidalia (GUI for Tor)
apt-get install vidalia deb.torproject.org-keyring

7. Install Privoxy
apt-get install privoxy
vim /etc/privoxy/config (uncomment line 1257) VIM Command Go To Line: 1257+G

8. Stop Privoxy
kill -9 (privoxy pid) 

9. Start Privoxy
/usr/sbin/privoxy --pidfile /var/run/privoxy.pid âuser privoxy /etc/privoxy/config

10. Firefox Settings: HTTP Proxy: 127.0.0.1 Port 8118 â Use this proxy server for all protocols
